# Xevio Advertorial Builder - Development Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router)
- React 19 + TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4 (OKLch colors, CSS custom properties)
- shadcn/ui components (New York style)
- @dnd-kit for drag-and-drop
- react-hook-form + Zod for form validation
- Supabase for backend (auth, DB, realtime)
- n8n for automation workflows (scraping, generation)
- Vercel for deployment

## Design Tokens
- Brand Teal: #0dadb7 (icons, accents)
- Brand Purple: #4644B6 (CTAs, active states)
- Brand Gray: #F6F6F6 (backgrounds)
- Font: Inter

## Key Principles
- Keep components simple and maintainable
- Use shadcn/ui for ALL UI primitives — never raw HTML inputs/buttons
- Icons from lucide-react only
- Use cn() from @/lib/utils for conditional classes
- All state management via React hooks in app/page.tsx (no Redux/Zustand)
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Props down, callbacks up for component communication
- Supabase Realtime for async updates (scraping status, etc.)

## Code Style
- Components: "use client", PascalCase names, kebab-case filenames
- Functions: camelCase
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase (in lib/types.ts)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Path aliases: @/components, @/lib, @/components/ui

## File Structure
- app/ — Next.js pages, layouts, and API routes
- components/ — Feature components (step-*.tsx, mode-*.tsx, etc.)
- components/ui/ — shadcn/ui primitives (do not edit manually)
- lib/ — Utilities (types.ts, supabase.ts, auth.ts, utils.ts, url-utils.ts)
- docs/ — Developer docs, feature reference
- n8n/ — n8n workflow JSONs and code snippets
- public/ — Static assets and images

## External Integrations
- Supabase: auth (email/password), campaigns table, realtime subscriptions
- n8n: 3 webhooks (scrape, generate, lazy-generate) — server-side only
- Google Docs: current output destination (v2 will add in-app editor)

## Do / Don't
- DO read existing component code before modifying — patterns are consistent
- DO use shadcn/ui for new UI (npx shadcn@latest add <component>)
- DO reference docs/.features for the full feature spec
- DO check docs/ for n8n payload structures before modifying API routes
- DON'T introduce new state management libraries without discussion
- DON'T modify components/ui/ files directly (shadcn-managed)
- DON'T expose n8n webhook URLs or secrets to client-side code
- DON'T break the existing wizard flow — there are live users

## Current Status
- Full 6-step wizard: complete (Full mode + Lazy mode)
- Authentication: complete (Supabase Auth, email/password)
- Backend integration: complete (n8n webhooks for scraping & generation)
- Supabase Realtime: complete (async scraping status updates)
- v2 planned: AI editing environment, LLM switching, more building blocks, n8n rework